- **Carrick Therapeutics Announces First Patient Dosed in Phase 1 Clinical Trial of CT7439 (CDK12/13 Inhibitor)**  
  - URL: `https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase`  
  - Quote snippets:  
    - “CT7439 is an inhibitor of CDK12/13 as well as a 'glue degrader' of Cyclin-K”  
    - “Clinical trial details can also be found on www.clinicaltrials.gov under study ID: NCT06600789.” ([carricktherapeutics.com](https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase?utm_source=openai))

    - “we report the discovery of ZLC491 as a potent, selective, and orally bioavailable CDK12/13 PROTAC degrader.”  
    - “doi: 10.1021/acs.jmedchem.4c01596” ([pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11513923/?utm_source=openai))
